\f1\b \cf0 Core Pipeline\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/Desktop/PhD/CORAL/Codes/src_codes/pipeline.py"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2 \cf4 \ul \ulc4 pipeline.py}}
\f0\b0  The main orchestrator, containing two pipeline classes:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f3 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
MutationExtractionPipeline
\f0  \'97 the 3-species pipeline: downloads genomes 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  fragments ingroup genomes into simulated reads 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  aligns to outgroup 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  pileup 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  extracts 3-mer/5-mer mutations 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  normalizes 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  plots 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  cleans up. Times and logs memory at each stage.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
MultiSpeciesMutationPipeline
\f0  \'97 N-species version: parses a Newick tree or species list, runs the same align/pileup steps, then uses Fitch parsimony to assign mutations to tree branches, and runs PHYLIP for phylogenetic reconstruction.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Managers (one responsibility each)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/Desktop/PhD/CORAL/Codes/src_codes/genome_manager.py"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2 \cf4 \ul \ulc4 genome_manager.py}}
\f0\b0  
\f3 Genome
\f0  class \'97 downloads a genome assembly from NCBI using 
\f3 datasets
\f0 , indexes it for BWA/bwa-mem2 (or just 
\f3 samtools faidx
\f0  for minimap2), and fragments the FASTA into overlapping simulated short reads written as a FASTQ.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/Desktop/PhD/CORAL/Codes/src_codes/alignment_manager.py"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\b \cf4 \ul \ulc4 alignment_manager.py}} 
\f3 Aligner
\f0  class \'97 aligns a species' fragmented FASTQ to the reference genome using BWA, bwa-mem2, minimap2, or bbmap. Two modes:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
align_streamed
\f0 : pipes aligner 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  filter 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  sort in one pass (memory-efficient)\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
align_disk_cached
\f0 : saves a raw BAM first, then filters it\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Also contains 
\f3 filter_sam
\f0  (simple MAPQ filter) and 
\f3 with_continuity_filter_sam
\f0  (the key filter: keeps low-MAPQ reads if they overlap with a high-MAPQ read of the same fragment from the adjacent position \'97 the "continuity" heuristic to rescue reads at species-specific loci).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/Desktop/PhD/CORAL/Codes/src_codes/pileup_manager.py"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\b \cf4 \ul \ulc4 pileup_manager.py}} 
\f3 Pileup
\f0  class \'97 runs 
\f3 samtools mpileup
\f0  across all aligned BAMs against the reference, compresses the output to 
\f3 .pileup.gz
\f0 . This is the data structure all mutation extraction reads from.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/Desktop/PhD/CORAL/Codes/src_codes/mutation_extractor_manager.py"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\b \cf4 \ul \ulc4 mutation_extractor_manager.py}} Three extractors for the 2-species case:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f3 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
MutationExtractor
\f0  \'97 scans the pileup with a 3-position sliding window; identifies sites where exactly one species differs from the outgroup and calls the 3-mer context mutation (e.g. 
\f3 A[C>T]G
\f0 ). Writes per-species JSON counts and full CSV.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
FiveMerExtractor
\f0  \'97 same idea but uses a 5-position window for 5-mer context mutations.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
TripletExtractor
\f0  \'97 counts 3-mer background contexts (not currently used in the pipeline, commented out).\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
MutationNormalizer
\f0  \'97 loads the mutation JSONs and triplet JSONs, collapses to pyrimidine-context (C/T ref), normalizes mutation counts by triplet frequency, and exports TSV tables for plotting.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/Desktop/PhD/CORAL/Codes/src_codes/multiple_species_mutation_extractor_manager.py"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\b \cf4 \ul \ulc4 multiple_species_mutation_extractor_manager.py}} 
\f3 MultipleSpeciesMutationExtractor
\f0  \'97 the N-species version. Scans the pileup for positions where all flanking bases agree across species but the central base varies, building a 
\f3 matching_bases.csv.gz
\f0 . Then applies Fitch parsimony on the phylogenetic tree to assign each variable site to a specific branch, collecting per-branch mutation spectra. Saves per-branch CSVs and spectra plots.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
