\f1\b \cf0 Utilities & Support\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/Desktop/PhD/CORAL/Codes/src_codes/cleanup_manager.py"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2 \cf4 \ul \ulc4 cleanup_manager.py}}
\f0\b0  
\f3 PipelineCleaner
\f0  \'97 deletes intermediate files after the pipeline runs: raw BAMs, the pileup, genome FASTA/FASTQ folders, interval files. Called at the end of 
\f3 MutationExtractionPipeline.run()
\f0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/Desktop/PhD/CORAL/Codes/src_codes/multiple_species_utils.py"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\b \cf4 \ul \ulc4 multiple_species_utils.py}} Tree/species utilities used by the multi-species pipeline:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f3 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
parse_species_accession_from_newick
\f0  \'97 extracts 
\f3 Species|Accession
\f0  leaf names from a Newick string and auto-detects the outgroup.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
annotate_tree_with_indices
\f0  / 
\f3 annotate_list_with_indices
\f0  \'97 assigns numeric indices to terminals (outgroup = 0, rest alphabetical), used to match pileup columns to tree leaves.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
save_annotated_tree
\f0  \'97 writes the index-annotated tree to disk.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
collapse_mutations
\f0  \'97 converts all mutations to pyrimidine-ref strand convention.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
load_random_rows
\f0  \'97 randomly samples up to 1M rows from a gzipped CSV (for PHYLIP input size limits).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/Desktop/PhD/CORAL/Codes/src_codes/run_phylip.py"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\b \cf4 \ul \ulc4 run_phylip.py}} Wraps the PHYLIP 
\f3 dnapars
\f0  (or other) executable:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Writes the mutation matrix as a PHYLIP-format 
\f3 infile
\f0 .\
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Runs PHYLIP twice: once without a starting tree (finds the most parsimonious tree) and once with the input Newick tree (scores that topology).\
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Compares parsimony scores to assess whether the given species tree is the most parsimonious explanation of the observed mutations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://claude.ai/epitaxy/Desktop/PhD/CORAL/Codes/src_codes/plot_utils.py"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\b \cf4 \ul \ulc4 plot_utils.py}} Three plotters:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
MutationSpectraPlotter
\f0  \'97 bar plots of 96-class (3-mer) or 5-mer mutation spectra, color-coded by mutation type; overlay comparison for 2 species.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
CoveragePlotter
\f0  \'97 sliding-window read coverage plot along a chromosome, computed from the interval TSV files.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
MutationDensityPlotter
\f0  \'97 sliding-window mutation density along a chromosome, optionally filtered by mutation category (e.g. CpG transitions) and optionally normalized by coverage.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
